That algorithm can be de-obfuscated (see my top level post for the intuition).  The above is equivalent to calculating a power of a 2x2 matrix, and since matrix multiplication is associative, we can use the squaring trick.<p>In python (I left out the code for matrix multiplication for brevity) this becomes<p><pre><code>  def nth_power_assoc(comp, f, n):
    &quot;&quot;&quot;Reduce n copies of f with associative operation comp (short for composition, not compare).&quot;&quot;&quot;
    if n < 1:
      raise ValueError
    if n == 1:
      return f
    if n % 2 == 1:
      return comp(nth_power_assoc(comp, f, n - 1), f)
    else:
      g = nth_power_assoc(comp, f, n / 2)
      return comp(g, g)

